Viral hepatitis markers as well as HIV antibodies were negative. Coproculture showed no pre absence of germs, the copro- parasitological examination excluded the presence of parasites. Complete colonoscopy with terminal ileum visualization revealed no mucosal abnormalities. Upper digestive endoscopy showed the loss of Kerckring folds in the descending duodenum. 
Small-bowel biopsies were obtained from the second part of the duodenum and send for histopathologic interpretation. Abdominal ultrasound was performed, with no abnormalities. Based on the endoscopy findings, correlated with clinical and biological data, infectious diarrhea, intestinal parasitoses, inflammatory bowel disease, pancreatic insufficiency, malignancies, were ruled out.